      },
      "date": "2014-04-21 17:06:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2\n\nSurely this one line patch does not need to be so far back in the series, or even part of the series?  It would be much easier to land if it were separate.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "76d9d3b3fb2a25a61d3a282cb64f9a12c60392a6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-04-21 23:12:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIn fact, this patch does not depends on others, but some others depend on both this patch and other patches (some have been landed recently). Moving this patch out of the series will simplify this patch's landing, but complex the dependence for others. That is why all of them were made in the same stack.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
